node.text: Topped with a colorful mix of tropical fruit, toasted nuts, and seeds, these open-faced chocolate disks from chef Paola Velez (@smallorchids) can be made ahead and served right from the fridge. Plus, they come together with the help of none other than your microwave! Find out how to make Tropical Mendiants by visiting this link https://bit.ly/2VLcZMq or tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

Tap the link in bio to get the recipe!

node.text: The secret to these flavor-packed, plant-based nachos from @chefmamacass2 are two different kinds of lentils: black and red. Crispy pita chips are smothered with an the irresistable feta queso, layers of pepper-tinged lentil chili, rose harissa-spiked pickled cabbage, and dollops of yogurt. It's definitely a dish worth sharing. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.title: FWCooks | Loaded Pita Nachos with Lentil Chili and Feta Queso

node.text: Topped with a colorful mix of tropical fruit, toasted nuts, and seeds, these open-faced chocolate disks from chef Paola Velez (@smallorchids) can be made ahead and served right from the fridge. Plus, they come together with the help of none other than your microwave! Find out how to make Tropical Mendiants by visiting this link https://bit.ly/2VLcZMq or tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.text: Have some leftover tomato paste lying around? Well, we have some ideas on how to put the classic pantry staple to use. From customized Bloody Mary mix to vinaigrettes and marinades, tap the link in bio for helpful suggestions to get the most out of that little can (or tube). 📸: @gettyimages

🍽️: Sally Sampson 📸: @alphamay

node.text: Mad Genius @justinchapple whips up paletas featuring prickly pears (also known as cactus pears), fresh lime juice and light agave nectar. These Mexican-style ice pops come out smooth, vibrantly colored, and subtly sweet. Tap the link in bio to learn how to make them at home.

Do you want to know the secret to Japanese soufflé pancakes? Achieving the high rise is all about speed and temperature—a mix of time and science! Click the link in our bio to get all the tips plus the recipe you'll have on repeat. 
🥞: Jack Poon & Sung Taek 📸: @gregdupree

node.text: Layers of eggplant, plum tomatoes, and fresh sliced Mozzarella get baked with toasty breadcrumbs and marinara sauce in this easy Sheet Pan Eggplant Parmesan recipe. Click the link in our bio for this tasty recipe! 📸: @protazio

node.text: Marinated in buttermilk, hot sauce, and dredged in cayenne-scented cornmeal, Mom’s Fried Catfish with Hot Sauce from @cheftoddrichards is crispy, crunchy and best served with a cold dark beer or a dry Riesling. Tap the link in bio to plan the next Friday night fish fry! 📸: @protazio

node.text: We can't resist peaches when they reach their peak! Whether to sweeten barbecue sauce for jerk-smoked duck, or grilled for an indulgent ice cream sundae, we are peechy keen for this juicy fruit. Tap the link in bio for 36 of our favorite recipes to incorporate the fresh, stone fruits into our meals. 📸: @jencausey

node.text:
This Caramelized Five-Onion Dip is a mix of five different alliums—shallots, scallions, and sweet, yellow, and red onions—that give the classic an upgrade with layers of flavor. Served with chips, toasted bread, or vegetables, it's perfect for that thing you were invited to this weekend. Tap the link in bio for the recipe. 
🧅: @justinchapple 📸: @protazio

node.text: Cool off with this Cold Crab Spaghetti from @toupsmeatery. Sweet fresh jumbo lump crabmeat is tossed with segments of juicy tangerine, a touch of Thai chile for heat and a flurry of mint, basil, and parsley. A garnish of trout roe makes this cool pasta dish POP! Tap the link in bio for the recipe. 📸: @ericwolfinger
